<taxonomicName authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1900" box="[297,436,1088,1111]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Didelphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pernigra">
<emphasis box="[297,436,1088,1111]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">D. pernigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) as a distinct species from the predominantly lowland taxon 
<taxonomicName authority="Lund" authorityName="Lund" authorityYear="1840" box="[123,362,1146,1170]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Didelphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albiventris">
<emphasis box="[123,287,1147,1170]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">D. albiventris</emphasis>
Lund
</taxonomicName>
, with which it was formerly synonymized (e.g., by Gardner, 1993).
</paragraph>
